Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.73,English,,0,0,0,,- Mathematics began as a way to quantify our world,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.73,0:00:04.91,English,,0,0,0,,to measure land,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.73,0:00:04.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.91,0:00:08.48,English,,0,0,0,,predict the motions of planets, and keep track of commerce.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.91,0:00:08.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.48,0:00:11.59,English,,0,0,0,,Then came a problem considered impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.48,0:00:11.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.59,0:00:14.45,English,,0,0,0,,The secret to solving it was to separate math
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.59,0:00:14.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.45,0:00:18.22,English,,0,0,0,,from the real world, to split algebra from geometry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.45,0:00:18.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.22,0:00:20.84,English,,0,0,0,,and to invent new numbers so fanciful
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.22,0:00:20.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.84,0:00:23.02,English,,0,0,0,,they are called imaginary.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.84,0:00:23.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:26.75,English,,0,0,0,,Ironically, 400 years later, these very numbers turn up
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:26.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.75,0:00:30.40,English,,0,0,0,,in the heart of our best physical theory of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.75,0:00:30.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:33.94,English,,0,0,0,,Only by abandoning math's connection to reality
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.40,0:00:33.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.94,0:00:36.95,English,,0,0,0,,could we discover reality's true nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.94,0:00:36.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.72,0:00:41.29,English,,0,0,0,,In 1494, Luca Pacioli
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.72,0:00:41.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.29,0:00:44.19,English,,0,0,0,,who is Leonardo da Vinci's math teacher publishes
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.29,0:00:44.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.19,0:00:47.56,English,,0,0,0,,"Summa de Arithmetica," a comprehensive summary
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.19,0:00:47.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:51.23,English,,0,0,0,,of all mathematics known in Renaissance Italy at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.56,0:00:51.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.23,0:00:53.38,English,,0,0,0,,In it, there's a section on the cubic,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.23,0:00:53.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.38,0:00:56.37,English,,0,0,0,,any equation which today we would write as ax cubed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.38,0:00:56.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.37,0:01:00.20,English,,0,0,0,,plus bx squared plus cx plus d equals zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.37,0:01:00.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:02.55,English,,0,0,0,,People have been trying to find a general solution
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.20,0:01:02.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.55,0:01:05.63,English,,0,0,0,,to the cubic for at least 4,000 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.55,0:01:05.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.63,0:01:08.10,English,,0,0,0,,but each ancient civilization that encountered it,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.63,0:01:08.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.10,0:01:10.43,English,,0,0,0,,the Babylonians, Greeks, Chinese,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.10,0:01:10.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.43,0:01:12.74,English,,0,0,0,,Indians, Egyptians, and Persians,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.43,0:01:12.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.74,0:01:15.38,English,,0,0,0,,they all came up empty-handed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.74,0:01:15.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.38,0:01:17.99,English,,0,0,0,,Pacioli's conclusion is that a solution
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.38,0:01:17.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.99,0:01:21.41,English,,0,0,0,,to the cubic equation is impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.99,0:01:21.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.41,0:01:23.37,English,,0,0,0,,Now, this should be at least a little surprising,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.41,0:01:23.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.37,0:01:25.13,English,,0,0,0,,since without the X cubed term,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.37,0:01:25.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.13,0:01:27.20,English,,0,0,0,,the equation is simply a quadratic.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.13,0:01:27.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.20,0:01:29.31,English,,0,0,0,,And many ancient civilizations
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.20,0:01:29.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.31,0:01:32.62,English,,0,0,0,,had solved quadratics thousands of years earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.31,0:01:32.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.62,0:01:34.61,English,,0,0,0,,Today, anyone who's passed eighth grade
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.62,0:01:34.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.61,0:01:36.26,English,,0,0,0,,knows the general solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.61,0:01:36.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.26,0:01:39.34,English,,0,0,0,,It's minus b plus minus root b squared minus four ac
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.26,0:01:39.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.34,0:01:41.17,English,,0,0,0,,all over two a.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.34,0:01:41.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.17,0:01:44.25,English,,0,0,0,,But most people just plug and chug into this formula
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.17,0:01:44.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.25,0:01:46.84,English,,0,0,0,,completely oblivious to the geometry
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.25,0:01:46.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.84,0:01:50.32,English,,0,0,0,,that ancient mathematicians used to derive it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.84,0:01:50.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.32,0:01:52.08,English,,0,0,0,,You know, back in those days,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.32,0:01:52.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.08,0:01:54.81,English,,0,0,0,,mathematics wasn't written down in equations.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.08,0:01:54.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.81,0:01:58.22,English,,0,0,0,,It was written with words and pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.81,0:01:58.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.22,0:01:59.05,English,,0,0,0,,Take, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.22,0:01:59.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.05,0:02:03.05,English,,0,0,0,,the equation x squared plus 26x equals 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.05,0:02:03.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.05,0:02:06.48,English,,0,0,0,,Ancient mathematicians would think of the x squared term
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.05,0:02:06.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:10.98,English,,0,0,0,,like a literal square with sides of length x.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.48,0:02:10.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.98,0:02:12.67,English,,0,0,0,,And then 26x,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.98,0:02:12.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.67,0:02:17.01,English,,0,0,0,,well, that would be a rectangle with one side of length 26
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.67,0:02:17.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.01,0:02:19.78,English,,0,0,0,,and the other side of length x,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.01,0:02:19.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.78,0:02:24.43,English,,0,0,0,,and these two areas together add to 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.78,0:02:24.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.43,0:02:26.88,English,,0,0,0,,So how do we figure out what x is?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.43,0:02:26.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:31.88,English,,0,0,0,,Well, we can take this 26x rectangle and cut it in half.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.88,0:02:31.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.29,0:02:38.23,English,,0,0,0,,So now I have two 13x rectangles and I can position them
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.29,0:02:38.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.23,0:02:41.42,English,,0,0,0,,so the new shape I create is almost a square,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.23,0:02:41.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.42,0:02:44.25,English,,0,0,0,,It's just missing this section down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.42,0:02:44.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.25,0:02:46.16,English,,0,0,0,,But I know the dimensions of this section.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.25,0:02:46.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:48.45,English,,0,0,0,,It's just 13 by 13.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.16,0:02:48.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.45,0:02:52.41,English,,0,0,0,,So I can complete the square by adding in
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.45,0:02:52.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.41,0:02:55.97,English,,0,0,0,,a 13 by 13 square.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.41,0:02:55.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:02:57.86,English,,0,0,0,,Now, since I've added 13-squared
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.97,0:02:57.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:03:01.45,English,,0,0,0,,or 169 to the left-hand side of the equation,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.86,0:03:01.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.45,0:03:03.48,English,,0,0,0,,I also have to add 169
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.45,0:03:03.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:05.98,English,,0,0,0,,to the right-hand side of the equation
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.48,0:03:05.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.98,0:03:07.67,English,,0,0,0,,to maintain the equality.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.98,0:03:07.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.67,0:03:09.64,English,,0,0,0,,So now I have this larger square
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.67,0:03:09.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:13.91,English,,0,0,0,,with sides of length X plus 13, and it is equal to 196.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:13.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.47,0:03:19.70,English,,0,0,0,,Now the square root of 196 is 14.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.47,0:03:19.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.70,0:03:23.33,English,,0,0,0,,So I know that the sides of this square have length 14,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.70,0:03:23.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.33,0:03:26.82,English,,0,0,0,,which means X is equal to one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.33,0:03:26.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:32.67,English,,0,0,0,,Now this is a great visual way to solve a quadratic equation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.82,0:03:32.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一种非常直观的二次方程的解法
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.67,0:03:34.87,English,,0,0,0,,but it isn't complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.67,0:03:34.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它并不完整
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.91,0:03:37.08,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you look at our original equation,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.91,0:03:37.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你仔细看看原始的方程
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.08,0:03:39.82,English,,0,0,0,,x equals one is a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.08,0:03:39.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,x=1确实是一个解
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:42.96,English,,0,0,0,,But so is negative 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.82,0:03:42.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是还有另一个解是x=-27
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.96,0:03:46.62,English,,0,0,0,,For thousands of years, mathematicians were oblivious
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.96,0:03:46.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几千年来  数学家们都无视了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:49.43,English,,0,0,0,,to the negative solutions to their equations
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.62,0:03:49.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,方程的负数解
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.43,0:03:52.02,English,,0,0,0,,because they were dealing with things in the real world,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.43,0:03:52.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为他们正尝试用数学解决实际问题
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:54.13,English,,0,0,0,,lengths and areas and volumes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.02,0:03:54.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,长度  面积  体积
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.13,0:03:56.65,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, what would it mean to have a square
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.65,0:03:59.59,English,,0,0,0,,with sides of length negative 27?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.13,0:03:59.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,边长为-27的正方形在现实中能表示什么呢
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:02.08,English,,0,0,0,,That just doesn't make any sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.59,0:04:02.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这完全没有意义
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.08,0:04:06.36,English,,0,0,0,,So for those mathematicians, negative numbers didn't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.08,0:04:06.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此对于当时的数学家来说  负数解并不存在
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.36,0:04:07.32,English,,0,0,0,,You could subtract,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.36,0:04:07.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以做减法
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.32,0:04:09.93,English,,0,0,0,,that is find the difference between two positive quantities,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.32,0:04:09.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,寻找两个正数之间的差异
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.93,0:04:11.74,English,,0,0,0,,but you couldn't have a negative answer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.93,0:04:11.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但你不能得到一个为负的答案
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.74,0:04:13.63,English,,0,0,0,,or negative coefficients.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.74,0:04:13.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者负系数
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.63,0:04:15.96,English,,0,0,0,,Mathematicians were so averse to negative numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.63,0:04:15.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,数学家们非常厌恶负数
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:19.54,English,,0,0,0,,that there was no single quadratic equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:19.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以至于二次方程没有一般式
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.54,0:04:21.88,English,,0,0,0,,Instead, there were six different versions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.54,0:04:21.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而是产生了6个不同的方程
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.88,0:04:25.82,English,,0,0,0,,arranged so that the coefficients were always positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.88,0:04:25.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以保证所有的系数都为正
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:28.35,English,,0,0,0,,The same approach was taken with the cubic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.82,0:04:28.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三次方程也采用了相同的处理方法
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:30.66,English,,0,0,0,,In the 11th century, Persian mathematician
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.35,0:04:30.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,11世纪中期  波斯数学家
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.66,0:04:36.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(290,563)\fad(500,500)}奥马尔·海亚姆
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:34.80,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}identified 19 different cubic equations,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.75,0:04:34.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}确定了19种不同的三次方程
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:37.61,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}again, keeping all coefficients positive.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:37.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}同样保证所有的系数都为正
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.61,0:04:39.68,English,,0,0,0,,He found numerical solutions to some of them
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.61,0:04:39.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他通过分析几何图形的交点
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.68,0:04:41.77,English,,0,0,0,,by considering the intersections of shapes,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.68,0:04:41.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,找到了其中一些方程的解
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.77,0:04:43.96,English,,0,0,0,,like hyperbolas and circles,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.77,0:04:43.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,例如双曲线和圆
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.96,0:04:46.21,English,,0,0,0,,but he fell short of his ultimate goal,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.96,0:04:46.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他仍无法达到他的最终目标
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:48.51,English,,0,0,0,,a general solution to the cubic.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.21,0:04:48.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三次方程的一般解
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.51,0:04:49.18,English,,0,0,0,,He wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.51,0:04:49.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他写道
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.18,0:04:51.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“也许在我们之后的某个人
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.10,0:04:53.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以成功地解开这个问题”
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:04:56.23,English,,0,0,0,,400 years later and 4,000 kilometers away,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.49,0:04:56.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,400年之后  在4000公里之外
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:04:58.64,English,,0,0,0,,the solution begins to take shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:04:58.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,答案逐渐开始成型
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.32,0:05:05.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,563)\fad(500,500)}希皮奥内·德尔·费罗
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.75,0:05:04.65,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}is a mathematics professor at the University of Bologna.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.75,0:05:04.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}是博洛尼亚大学的一位数学教授
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:07.28,English,,0,0,0,,Sometime around 1510,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.50,0:05:07.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1510年左右
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:11.61,English,,0,0,0,,he finds a method to reliably solve depressed cubics.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.28,0:05:11.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他找到了“弱三次方程”的通用解法
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.61,0:05:13.68,English,,0,0,0,,These are a subset of cubic equations
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.61,0:05:13.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一类特殊的三次方程
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.68,0:05:16.14,English,,0,0,0,,with no X squared term.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.68,0:05:16.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有二次项
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.14,0:05:18.83,English,,0,0,0,,So what does he do after solving a problem that has stumped
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.14,0:05:18.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,困扰了数学家们几千年的问题被他解决后
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.83,0:05:20.37,English,,0,0,0,,mathematicians from millennia?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.83,0:05:20.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他又做了什么呢
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.37,0:05:21.89,English,,0,0,0,,One considered impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.37,0:05:21.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一个被达芬奇的数学老师
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.89,0:05:24.28,English,,0,0,0,,by Leonardo da Vinci's math teacher?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.89,0:05:24.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,认为是不可能解决的问题
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.34,0:05:28.10,English,,0,0,0,,He tells no one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.34,0:05:28.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他缄口如瓶
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.10,0:05:31.45,English,,0,0,0,,See, being a mathematician in the 1500s is hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.10,0:05:31.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在16世纪  当个数学家非常难
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.45,0:05:33.28,English,,0,0,0,,Your job is constantly under threat
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.45,0:05:33.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你的工作会不断受到威胁
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:36.22,English,,0,0,0,,from other mathematicians who can show up at any time
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:36.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其他数学家随时都可能出现
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.22,0:05:38.46,English,,0,0,0,,and challenge you for your position.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.22,0:05:38.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后挑战你的地位
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.46,0:05:41.11,English,,0,0,0,,You can think of it like a math duel.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.46,0:05:41.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以理解成一种数学决斗
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.11,0:05:44.14,English,,0,0,0,,Each participant submits a set of questions to the other,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.11,0:05:44.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,每一位参与者提交一组问题给对手
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.14,0:05:45.41,English,,0,0,0,,and the person who solves
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.41,0:05:48.23,English,,0,0,0,,the most questions correctly gets the job
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.14,0:05:48.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后解答正确数最多的那位获胜
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.23,0:05:51.29,English,,0,0,0,,while the loser suffers public humiliation.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.23,0:05:51.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而败者则会蒙受耻辱
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:53.96,English,,0,0,0,,As far as del Ferro knows,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.17,0:05:53.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,据德尔·费罗所知
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.96,0:05:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,no one else in the world can solve the depressed cubic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.96,0:05:57.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,世上没有其他人能解出弱三次方程
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:05:59.50,English,,0,0,0,,So by keeping his solutions secret,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.26,0:05:59.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因此  只要他对自己的解法保密
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.50,0:06:02.52,English,,0,0,0,,he guarantees his own job security.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.50,0:06:02.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即可保证自己的研究成果不被超越
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.52,0:06:06.58,English,,0,0,0,,For nearly two decades, del Ferro keeps his secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.52,0:06:06.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,德尔·费罗将他的秘密保守了近二十年
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.58,0:06:09.05,English,,0,0,0,,Only on his deathbed in 1526
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.58,0:06:09.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到1526年他临终前
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:11.05,English,,0,0,0,,does he let it slip to his student
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.05,0:06:11.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他才将解法透露给了他的学生
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.05,0:06:16.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(870,526)\fad(333,500)}安东尼奥·菲奥尔
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:16.10,English,,0,0,0,,Fior is not as talented a mathematician as his mentor,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:16.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,菲奥尔并不像他的导师那样有才华
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.10,0:06:18.38,English,,0,0,0,,but he is young and ambitious.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.10,0:06:18.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但他年轻而且野心勃勃
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.38,0:06:19.68,English,,0,0,0,,And after del Ferro's death,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.38,0:06:19.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在德尔·费罗死后
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:22.12,English,,0,0,0,,he boasts about his own mathematical prowess
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.68,0:06:22.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他吹嘘自己的数学能力
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.12,0:06:26.19,English,,0,0,0,,and specifically, his ability to solve the depressed cubic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.12,0:06:26.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且他大吹特吹  自己能解弱三次方程
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:28.48,English,,0,0,0,,On February 12, 1535,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.19,0:06:28.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.48,0:06:30.33,English,,0,0,0,,Fior challenges mathematician
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.48,0:06:30.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.70,0:06:34.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(445,523)\fad(333,500)}尼科洛·丰坦纳·塔尔塔利亚
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.36,0:06:36.11,English,,0,0,0,,who has recently moved to Fior's hometown of Venice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.36,0:06:36.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:39.58,English,,0,0,0,,Niccolo Fontana is no stranger to adversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.11,0:06:39.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.58,0:06:42.87,English,,0,0,0,,As a kid, his face was cut open by a French soldier,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.58,0:06:42.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.87,0:06:44.77,English,,0,0,0,,leaving him with a stutter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.87,0:06:44.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.77,0:06:46.69,English,,0,0,0,,That's why he's known as Tartaglia,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.77,0:06:46.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.69,0:06:49.26,English,,0,0,0,,which means stutterer in Italian.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.69,0:06:49.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:52.63,English,,0,0,0,,Growing up in poverty, Tartaglia is largely self-taught.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.26,0:06:52.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.63,0:06:54.91,English,,0,0,0,,He claws his way up through Italian society
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.63,0:06:54.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.91,0:06:57.74,English,,0,0,0,,to become a respected mathematician.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.91,0:06:57.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.74,0:07:00.98,English,,0,0,0,,Now, all of that is at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.74,0:07:00.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:03.45,English,,0,0,0,,As is the custom, in the challenge Tartaglia gives
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.98,0:07:06.83,English,,0,0,0,,a very discernment of 30 problems to Fior.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.45,0:07:06.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.83,0:07:09.63,English,,0,0,0,,Fior gives 30 problems to Tartaglia,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.83,0:07:09.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.63,0:07:12.09,English,,0,0,0,,all of which are depressed cubics.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.63,0:07:12.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.08,0:07:14.81,English,,0,0,0,,Each mathematician has 40 days
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.08,0:07:14.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.81,0:07:17.36,English,,0,0,0,,to solve the 30 problems they've been given.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.81,0:07:17.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.36,0:07:21.25,English,,0,0,0,,Fior can't solve a single problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.36,0:07:21.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:24.80,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia solves all 30 of Fior's depressed cubics
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.25,0:07:24.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:26.80,English,,0,0,0,,in just two hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.80,0:07:26.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:30.36,English,,0,0,0,,It seems Fior's boastfulness was his undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.80,0:07:30.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:32.82,English,,0,0,0,,Before the challenge came, Tartaglia learns
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.36,0:07:32.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.82,0:07:35.13,English,,0,0,0,,that Fior's claimed to have solved the depressed cubic,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.82,0:07:35.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.13,0:07:36.61,English,,0,0,0,,but he's skeptical.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.13,0:07:36.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.89,0:07:39.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,依我之见  他的能力不足以独立解出这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.89,0:07:41.15,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia writes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.11,0:07:41.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.15,0:07:43.02,English,,0,0,0,,But word was that a great mathematician
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.15,0:07:43.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.02,0:07:44.84,English,,0,0,0,,had revealed the secret to Fior,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.02,0:07:44.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.84,0:07:46.71,English,,0,0,0,,which seems more plausible.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.84,0:07:46.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:50.09,English,,0,0,0,,So with the knowledge that a solution to the cubic is possible,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.71,0:07:50.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.09,0:07:52.17,English,,0,0,0,,and with his livelihood on the line,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.09,0:07:52.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.17,0:07:56.07,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia sets about solving the depressed cubic himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.17,0:07:56.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.07,0:07:58.60,English,,0,0,0,,To do it, he extends the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.60,0:08:02.61,English,,0,0,0,,of completing the square into three dimensions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.07,0:08:02.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.61,0:08:07.09,English,,0,0,0,,Take the equation x cubed plus nine x equals 26.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.61,0:08:07.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.09,0:08:08.43,English,,0,0,0,,You can think of x cubed
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.09,0:08:08.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.43,0:08:11.86,English,,0,0,0,,as the volume of a cube with sides of length x.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.43,0:08:11.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.86,0:08:15.54,English,,0,0,0,,And if you add a volume of nine x, you get 26.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.86,0:08:15.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.54,0:08:17.46,English,,0,0,0,,So just like with completing the square,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.54,0:08:17.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.46,0:08:19.44,English,,0,0,0,,we need to add onto the cube
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.46,0:08:19.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.44,0:08:22.69,English,,0,0,0,,to increase its volume by nine x.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.44,0:08:22.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.69,0:08:27.27,English,,0,0,0,,Imagine extending three sides of this cube out a distance y,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.69,0:08:27.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.27,0:08:31.92,English,,0,0,0,,creating a new, larger cube with sides of length, call it z.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.27,0:08:31.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.92,0:08:34.68,English,,0,0,0,,z is just x plus y.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.92,0:08:34.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:36.90,English,,0,0,0,,The original cube has been padded out
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.68,0:08:36.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.90,0:08:41.20,English,,0,0,0,,and we can break up the additional volume into seven shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.90,0:08:41.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:43.22,English,,0,0,0,,There are three rectangular prisms
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.20,0:08:43.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.22,0:08:46.71,English,,0,0,0,,with dimensions of x by x by y,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.22,0:08:46.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:48.70,English,,0,0,0,,and another three narrower prisms
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:48.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.70,0:08:51.82,English,,0,0,0,,with dimensions of x by y by y,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.70,0:08:51.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:54.89,English,,0,0,0,,plus there's a cube with a volume y cubed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.82,0:08:54.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.89,0:08:59.72,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia rearranges the six rectangular prisms into one block.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.89,0:08:59.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.72,0:09:02.01,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}One side has length three y,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.72,0:09:02.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.01,0:09:05.28,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}the other has a length x plus y, which is z,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.01,0:09:05.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.28,0:09:07.40,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}and the height is x.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.28,0:09:07.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:08.84,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}So the volume of this shape
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.40,0:09:08.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:12.49,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}is its base, three yz times its height, x.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.84,0:09:12.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.49,0:09:16.01,English,,0,0,0,,And Tartaglia realizes this volume can perfectly represent
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.49,0:09:16.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:18.18,English,,0,0,0,,the nine x term in the equation,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.01,0:09:18.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.18,0:09:20.83,English,,0,0,0,,if its base is equal to nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.18,0:09:20.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.83,0:09:24.05,English,,0,0,0,,So he sets three yz equals nine.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.83,0:09:24.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.05,0:09:26.23,English,,0,0,0,,Putting the cube back together,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.05,0:09:26.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.23,0:09:29.38,English,,0,0,0,,you find we're missing the one small y cubed block,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.23,0:09:29.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.38,0:09:32.09,English,,0,0,0,,so we can complete the cube
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.09,0:09:35.34,English,,0,0,0,,by adding y cubed to both sides of the equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.38,0:09:35.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.34,0:09:38.32,English,,0,0,0,,Now we have z cubed, the complete larger cube,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.34,0:09:38.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:40.65,English,,0,0,0,,equals 26 plus y cubed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.32,0:09:40.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.65,0:09:43.90,English,,0,0,0,,We have two equations and two unknowns.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.65,0:09:43.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:45.52,English,,0,0,0,,Solving the first equation for z
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.90,0:09:45.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:47.14,English,,0,0,0,,and substituting into the second,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.52,0:09:47.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:51.83,English,,0,0,0,,we get y to the six plus 26 y cubed equals 27.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.14,0:09:51.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:54.67,English,,0,0,0,,At first glance, it seems like we're now worse off
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.83,0:09:54.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.67,0:09:55.77,English,,0,0,0,,than when we started.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.67,0:09:55.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.77,0:09:57.89,English,,0,0,0,,The variable is now raised to the power of six,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.77,0:09:57.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:09:59.49,English,,0,0,0,,instead of just three.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.89,0:09:59.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:02.99,English,,0,0,0,,However, if you think of y cubed as a new variable,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.49,0:10:02.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.99,0:10:06.04,English,,0,0,0,,the equation is actually a quadratic,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.99,0:10:06.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:09.78,English,,0,0,0,,the same quadratic that we solved by completing the square.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.04,0:10:09.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.78,0:10:12.33,English,,0,0,0,,So we know y cubed equals one,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.78,0:10:12.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:16.34,English,,0,0,0,,which means y equals one, and z equals three over y,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.33,0:10:16.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.34,0:10:17.90,English,,0,0,0,,so z is three.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.34,0:10:17.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.90,0:10:21.96,English,,0,0,0,,And since x plus y equals z, x must be equal to two,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.90,0:10:21.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.84,0:10:26.44,English,,0,0,0,,which is indeed, a solution to the original equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.84,0:10:26.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.44,0:10:27.28,English,,0,0,0,,And with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.44,0:10:27.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.28,0:10:30.03,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia becomes the second human on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.28,0:10:30.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.03,0:10:32.27,English,,0,0,0,,to solve the depressed cubic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.03,0:10:32.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.27,0:10:34.59,English,,0,0,0,,To save himself the work of going through the geometry
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.27,0:10:34.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:36.84,English,,0,0,0,,for each new cubic he encounters,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:36.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.84,0:10:39.88,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia summarizes his method in an algorithm,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.84,0:10:39.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.88,0:10:41.68,English,,0,0,0,,a set of instructions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.88,0:10:41.68,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.68,0:10:44.35,English,,0,0,0,,He writes this down not as a set of equations
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.68,0:10:44.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.35,0:10:45.39,English,,0,0,0,,like we would today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.35,0:10:45.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.39,0:10:47.44,English,,0,0,0,,Modern algebraic notation wouldn't exist
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.44,0:10:48.93,English,,0,0,0,,for another hundred years,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.39,0:10:48.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.93,0:10:50.91,English,,0,0,0,,but instead, as a poem.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.93,0:10:50.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.15,0:10:53.60,Poem,,0,0,0,,{\an4\pos(68,350)\fad(333,0)\fn20}若三次项并其后的一次项\N等于某个自然数\N则以该数为差值  寻甲乙两数\N接着  按照惯例\N甲乙之积总是会等于\N一次项系数之少半  自再乘\N剩余的步骤就是\N甲乙开立方  得值相减\N即为汝方程之未知数\N\N\N在第二种情况中\N三次项独立放一边\N你可以走另一条路\N常数项可拆为甲乙两数之和\N而甲乙之积仍直接等于
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.15,0:10:53.60,Poem,,0,0,0,,{\an4\pos(660,350)\fad(333,0)\fn20}一次项系数之少半  自再乘\N接着  出于常识\N开立方除甲并开立方除乙\N得和乃汝之未知数\N\N\N至于第三类计算\N则与第二类联立\N你若细心斟酌\N可见两式之解正负相抵\N\N\N我找到的方法\N用起来可不慢\N在一千五百三十四年\N凭借无比坚实的基础\N于此环海之城
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.15,0:10:53.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:55.83,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia's victory makes him something of a celebrity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.36,0:10:55.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.83,0:10:57.76,English,,0,0,0,,Mathematicians are desperate to learn
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.83,0:10:57.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:00.03,English,,0,0,0,,how he solved the cubic, especially
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.76,0:11:00.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.20,0:11:04.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(360,420)\fad(333,500)}吉罗拉莫·卡尔达诺
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.31,0:11:03.64,English,,0,0,0,,a polymath based in Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.31,0:11:03.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.64,0:11:06.31,English,,0,0,0,,As you can guess, Tartaglia will have none of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.64,0:11:06.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.31,0:11:10.31,English,,0,0,0,,He refuses to reveal even a single question from the competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.31,0:11:10.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:12.29,English,,0,0,0,,But Cardano is persistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:12.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.29,0:11:13.68,English,,0,0,0,,He writes a series of letters
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.29,0:11:13.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.68,0:11:17.83,English,,0,0,0,,that alternate between flattery and aggressive attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.68,0:11:17.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.83,0:11:20.11,English,,0,0,0,,Eventually with the promise of an introduction
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.11,0:11:21.80,English,,0,0,0,,to his wealthy benefactor,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.83,0:11:21.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:25.49,English,,0,0,0,,Cardono manages to lure Tartaglia to Milan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:25.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:28.09,English,,0,0,0,,And there on March 25, 1539
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.49,0:11:28.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.09,0:11:30.30,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia reveals his method,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.09,0:11:30.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.30,0:11:34.21,English,,0,0,0,,but only after forcing Cardono to swear a solemn oath
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.30,0:11:34.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:35.94,English,,0,0,0,,not to tell anyone the method,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.21,0:11:35.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.94,0:11:37.14,English,,0,0,0,,not to publish it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.94,0:11:37.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.14,0:11:39.67,English,,0,0,0,,and to write it only in cipher.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.14,0:11:39.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.67,0:11:42.24,English,,0,0,0,,Quote, "So that after my death,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.67,0:11:42.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.24,0:11:45.30,English,,0,0,0,,no one shall be able to understand it."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.24,0:11:45.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.30,0:11:46.92,English,,0,0,0,,Cardono is delighted
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.30,0:11:46.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.92,0:11:50.47,English,,0,0,0,,and immediately starts playing around with Tartaglia's algorithm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.92,0:11:50.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.47,0:11:52.74,English,,0,0,0,,But he has a loftier goal in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.47,0:11:52.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.74,0:11:57.05,English,,0,0,0,,a solution to the full cubic equation, including the x squared term.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.74,0:11:57.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.05,0:11:59.76,English,,0,0,0,,And amazingly, he discovers it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.05,0:11:59.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.76,0:12:01.70,English,,0,0,0,,If you substitute for x,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.76,0:12:01.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:04.06,English,,0,0,0,,x minus b over three a,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.70,0:12:04.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.06,0:12:07.27,English,,0,0,0,,then all the X squared terms cancel out.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.06,0:12:07.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:10.20,English,,0,0,0,,This is the way to turn any general cubic equation
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.27,0:12:10.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:11.88,English,,0,0,0,,into a depressed cubic,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.20,0:12:11.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.88,0:12:15.00,English,,0,0,0,,which can then be solved by Tartaglia's formula.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.88,0:12:15.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.00,0:12:17.57,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano is so excited to have solved the problem
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.00,0:12:17.57,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.57,0:12:20.39,English,,0,0,0,,that stumped the best mathematicians for thousands of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.57,0:12:20.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.39,0:12:22.28,English,,0,0,0,,he wants to publish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.39,0:12:22.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:23.21,English,,0,0,0,,Unlike his peers,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.28,0:12:23.21,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.21,0:12:26.12,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano has no need to keep the solution a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.21,0:12:26.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.12,0:12:28.62,English,,0,0,0,,He makes his living not as a mathematician,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.12,0:12:28.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.62,0:12:31.49,English,,0,0,0,,but as a physician and famous intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.62,0:12:31.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.49,0:12:35.51,English,,0,0,0,,For him, the credit is more valuable than the secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.49,0:12:35.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.51,0:12:39.10,English,,0,0,0,,The only problem is the oath he swore to Tartaglia
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.51,0:12:39.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.10,0:12:41.46,English,,0,0,0,,who won't let him break it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.10,0:12:41.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.46,0:12:43.73,English,,0,0,0,,And you might think this would be the end of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.46,0:12:43.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.73,0:12:47.79,English,,0,0,0,,But in 1542, Cardano travels to Bologna
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.73,0:12:47.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.79,0:12:49.65,English,,0,0,0,,and there he visits a mathematician
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.79,0:12:49.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.65,0:12:51.78,English,,0,0,0,,who just happens to be the son-in-law
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.65,0:12:51.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.78,0:12:55.70,English,,0,0,0,,of one Scipione del Ferro, the man who on his deathbed,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.78,0:12:55.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.70,0:12:59.37,English,,0,0,0,,gave the solution to the depressed cubic to Antonio Fior.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.70,0:12:59.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:02.75,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano finds the solution in del Ferro's old notebook,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:02.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.75,0:13:04.84,English,,0,0,0,,which is shared with him during the visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.75,0:13:04.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:08.02,English,,0,0,0,,This solution predates Tartaglia's by decades.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.84,0:13:08.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.02,0:13:09.75,English,,0,0,0,,So now, as Cardano sees it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.02,0:13:09.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.75,0:13:11.96,English,,0,0,0,,he can publish the full solution to the cubic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.75,0:13:11.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.96,0:13:15.50,English,,0,0,0,,without violating his oath to Tartaglia.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.96,0:13:15.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:16.47,English,,0,0,0,,Three years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.50,0:13:16.47,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.47,0:13:19.43,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano publishes "Ars Magna," The Great Art,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.47,0:13:19.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.43,0:13:21.89,English,,0,0,0,,an updated compendium of mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.43,0:13:21.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.89,0:13:27.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(640,490)}写就凡五载  流芳愿千年
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.96,0:13:28.83,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano writes a chapter with a unique geometric proof
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.96,0:13:28.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.83,0:13:32.25,English,,0,0,0,,for each of the 13 arrangements of the cubic equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.83,0:13:32.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.25,0:13:33.28,English,,0,0,0,,Although he acknowledges
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.25,0:13:33.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:36.59,English,,0,0,0,,the contributions of Tartaglia, del Ferro and Fior,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.28,0:13:36.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.59,0:13:39.95,English,,0,0,0,,Tartaglia is displeased, to say the least.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.59,0:13:39.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.95,0:13:41.83,English,,0,0,0,,He writes insulting letters to Cardano,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.95,0:13:41.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.50,0:13:45.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an4\pos(60,360)}无耻  无权无势的男人\N愚蠢至极的男人\N数学研究的门外汉
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:45.25,English,,0,0,0,,and CC's a good fraction of the mathematics community.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.83,0:13:45.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.25,0:13:46.32,English,,0,0,0,,And he has a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.25,0:13:46.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:48.59,English,,0,0,0,,To this day, the general solution to the cubic
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.32,0:13:48.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:51.78,English,,0,0,0,,is often called Cardano's method.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.59,0:13:51.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.78,0:13:54.90,English,,0,0,0,,But "Ars Magna" is a phenomenal achievement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.78,0:13:54.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.90,0:13:59.54,English,,0,0,0,,It pushes geometrical reasoning to its very breaking point.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.90,0:13:59.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:01.01,English,,0,0,0,,Literally.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.54,0:14:01.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:03.07,English,,0,0,0,,While Cardano is writing "Ars Magna"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.01,0:14:03.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在卡尔达诺写 "Ars Magna" 这本书的时候，
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:05.17,English,,0,0,0,,he comes across some cubic equations
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.17,0:14:08.27,English,,0,0,0,,that can't easily be solved in the usual way,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:08.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他发现了一些不能以正常方式解出答案的三次等式
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:11.91,English,,0,0,0,,like x cubed equals 15x plus four.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.27,0:14:11.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比如 x³ = 15x + 4
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.91,0:14:14.58,English,,0,0,0,,Plugging this into the algorithm yields a solution
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.58,0:14:17.89,English,,0,0,0,,that contains the square roots of negative numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.91,0:14:17.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,把这个放进算法里会算出含有负数平方根的答案。
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.89,0:14:20.22,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano asks Tartaglia about the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.89,0:14:20.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔达诺向塔尔塔利亚询问了这件事
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.22,0:14:22.27,English,,0,0,0,,but he evades and implies Cardano
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.22,0:14:22.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但塔尔塔利亚回避了这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:25.45,English,,0,0,0,,is just not clever enough to use his formula properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.27,0:14:25.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并表示卡尔达诺只是并不够聪明去正确使用他的等式
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.45,0:14:28.92,English,,0,0,0,,The reality is Tartaglia has no idea what to do either.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.45,0:14:28.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,真实的情况是，塔尔塔利亚也对这个问题一筹莫展
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.12,0:14:32.82,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano walks back through the geometric derivation
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.12,0:14:32.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔达诺回头重新看了相似问题的几何推导过程
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.82,0:14:36.95,English,,0,0,0,,of a similar problem to see exactly what goes wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.82,0:14:36.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,以求发现到底在哪里出现了问题
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.95,0:14:40.69,English,,0,0,0,,While the 3D cube slicing and rearrangement works just fine,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.95,0:14:40.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然用3D立方切片以及重新安排的方式正好能解决问题
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:43.36,English,,0,0,0,,the final quadratic completing the square step
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.69,0:14:43.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但在解最后的那一个填满正方形的二元方程式时
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.36,0:14:46.15,English,,0,0,0,,leads to a geometric paradox.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.36,0:14:46.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发生了一个几何上的矛盾
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:50.53,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano finds part of a square that must have an area of 30,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.15,0:14:50.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔达诺发现，正方形的面积必须是30
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:53.66,English,,0,0,0,,but also sides of length five.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.53,0:14:53.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但它的边长同时也必须是5
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.66,0:14:56.60,English,,0,0,0,,Since the full square has an area of 25,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.66,0:15:56.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为这整个正方形的面积是25
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:14:57.94,English,,0,0,0,,to complete the square,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:15:57.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要使这个正方形完整
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.94,0:15:02.46,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano has to somehow add negative area.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.66,0:15:02.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔达诺就必须用某种方式增加一些负面积
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:05.24,English,,0,0,0,,That is where the square roots of negatives come from,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.24,0:15:08.52,English,,0,0,0,,the idea of negative area.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:08.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是那个负平方根，亦即是负面积的概念出来的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:09.73,English,,0,0,0,,Now, this isn't the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.73,0:15:12.15,English,,0,0,0,,square roots of negatives show up in mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.52,0:15:12.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在，这不是第一次负平方根出现在数学里面
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:15.67,English,,0,0,0,,In fact, earlier in "Ars Magnae" is this problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.15,0:15:15.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上，这个问题在更早的《大术》中就已经出现了
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.67,0:15:19.96,English,,0,0,0,,Find two numbers that add to 10 and multiply to 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.67,0:15:19.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,要找到相加等于10，相乘等于40的两个数
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.96,0:15:22.50,English,,0,0,0,,You can combine these equations into the quadratic
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.50,0:15:25.55,English,,0,0,0,,X squared plus 40 equals 10 X.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.96,0:15:25.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以将这些等式结合为 x² + 40 = 10x
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:28.13,English,,0,0,0,,But if you plug this into the quadratic formula,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.55,0:15:28.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是如果你将这个式子代入二元方程公式
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.13,0:15:31.83,English,,0,0,0,,the solutions contain the square roots of negatives.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.13,0:15:31.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,解出来的答案将含有负的平方根
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.83,0:15:35.63,English,,0,0,0,,The obvious conclusion is that a solution doesn't exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.83,0:15:35.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很明显，这样的解根本不会存在
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.63,0:15:38.37,English,,0,0,0,,which you can verify by looking at the original problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.63,0:15:38.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以透过重新看原题来验证这个事实
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:40.33,English,,0,0,0,,There are no two real numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.33,0:15:42.82,English,,0,0,0,,which add to 10 and multiply to 40.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.37,0:15:42.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有两个实数既能在相加等于10的同时，相乘等于40
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.66,0:15:45.84,English,,0,0,0,,So mathematicians understood
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.66,0:15:45.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以数学家们知道
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.84,0:15:47.52,English,,0,0,0,,square roots of negative numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.52,0:15:51.31,English,,0,0,0,,were maths way of telling you there is no solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.84,0:15:51.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,负数的平方根是以数学的形式告诉你这个式子没有解
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.31,0:15:54.28,English,,0,0,0,,But this cubic equation is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.31,0:15:54.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这个三次等式是不一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:55.71,English,,0,0,0,,With the little guessing and checking,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.28,0:15:55.71,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在使用亿点点的猜想和查证下
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.71,0:15:59.70,English,,0,0,0,,you can find that x equals four is a solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.71,0:15:59.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你可以发现 x = 4 是一个解
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.70,0:16:02.83,English,,0,0,0,,So why doesn't the approach that works for all other cubics
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.70,0:16:02.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以为什么能适用于其他全部立方体的方法
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.83,0:16:06.52,English,,0,0,0,,find the perfectly reasonable solution to this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.83,0:16:06.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不能在这个等式上求出完美的合理的解呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:07.97,English,,0,0,0,,Unable to see a way forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.52,0:16:07.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为看不到有任何的出路
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.97,0:16:10.52,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano avoids this case in "Ars Magna"
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.97,0:16:10.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔达诺回避了在《大术》里面的这个问题
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.52,0:16:12.93,English,,0,0,0,,saying the idea of the square root of negatives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.93,0:16:15.36,English,,0,0,0,,"is as subtle as it is useless".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.52,0:16:15.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并表示负数平方根的概念 「是一种取巧且不必要」
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.91,0:16:19.35,English,,0,0,0,,But around 10 years later, the Italian engineer
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.91,0:16:19.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但10年之后，意大利的工程师拉斐尔.邦贝利
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.35,0:16:22.84,English,,0,0,0,,Rafael Bombelli picks up where Cardano left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.35,0:16:22.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在卡尔达诺停下的地方继续研究
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.84,0:16:24.65,English,,0,0,0,,Undeterred by the square roots of negatives
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.65,0:16:26.87,English,,0,0,0,,and the impossible geometry they imply,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.84,0:16:26.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为对负数平方根与它们能表达的不可能几何的坚信（？）
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.87,0:16:30.52,English,,0,0,0,,he wants to find a way through the mess to the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.87,0:16:30.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他想要找到到达题解中心的道路
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.52,0:16:32.36,English,,0,0,0,,Observing that the square root of a negative
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.52,0:16:32.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,观察一个负数平方根
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.36,0:16:35.37,English,,0,0,0,,"cannot be called either positive or negative",
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.36,0:16:35.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,“既不能不能被称为正，也不能被称为负”
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.37,0:16:39.10,English,,0,0,0,,he lets it be its own new type of number.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.37,0:16:39.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他定义这种数为一种新数类
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:41.67,English,,0,0,0,,Bombelli assumes the two terms in Cardano's solution
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.10,0:16:41.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,邦贝利设想在卡尔达诺的解中的这两个术语
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.67,0:16:43.92,English,,0,0,0,,can be represented as some combination
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.92,0:16:46.59,English,,0,0,0,,of an ordinary number and this new type of number,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.67,0:16:46.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,能以某种组合普通数及这种新数的方式呈现
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.59,0:16:49.13,English,,0,0,0,,which involves the square root of negative one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.59,0:16:49.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这能将负数平方根包含在解里面
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.13,0:16:51.35,English,,0,0,0,,And this way, Bombelli figures out
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.13,0:16:51.35,Chinese,,0,0,0,,透过这种方式，邦贝利发现
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.35,0:16:53.90,English,,0,0,0,,that the two cube roots in Cardano's equation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.35,0:16:53.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这两个在卡尔达诺等式的立方根
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.90,0:16:55.11,English,,0,0,0,,are equivalent to two
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.11,0:16:57.52,English,,0,0,0,,plus or minus the square root of negative one.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.90,0:16:57.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,等价于两个加或减那个负数平方根
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.52,0:17:00.06,English,,0,0,0,,So when he takes the final step and adds them together,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.52,0:17:00.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样当他执行那最后一步，将它们加起来之后
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:01.52,English,,0,0,0,,the square roots cancel out,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.06,0:17:01.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个平方根就被消掉了
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.52,0:17:04.43,English,,0,0,0,,leaving the correct answer, four.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.52,0:17:04.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,流下了正确的答案，4
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.43,0:17:07.08,English,,0,0,0,,This feels nothing short of miraculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.43,0:17:07.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这种方式感觉没有任何的奇思妙想（？）
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.08,0:17:09.01,English,,0,0,0,,Cardano's method does work,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.08,0:17:09.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,卡尔达诺的方式的确能解决问题
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.01,0:17:11.37,English,,0,0,0,,but you have to abandon the geometric proof
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.37,0:17:13.96,English,,0,0,0,,that generated it in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.01,0:17:13.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但你必须要抛弃在第一步生成几何证明
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.96,0:17:16.93,English,,0,0,0,,Negative areas, which make no sense in reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.96,0:17:16.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,负平面，这个在真实世界上没有任何意义的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.93,0:17:19.35,English,,0,0,0,,must exist as an intermediate step
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.35,0:17:21.45,English,,0,0,0,,on the way to the solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.93,0:17:21.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是一定得作为一个在通往答案的中间步骤而存在的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.45,0:17:25.03,English,,0,0,0,,Over the next hundred years, modern mathematics takes shape.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.45,0:17:25.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在下一个百年中，现代数学开始成型
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.03,0:17:26.34,English,,0,0,0,,In the 1600s,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.03,0:17:26.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在17世纪
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.34,0:17:31.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(287,533)\fad(500,500)}弗朗索瓦·韦达
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:30.44,English,,0,0,0,,introduces the modern symbolic notation for algebra,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.20,0:17:30.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,引入了代数的现代符号标记法
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:32.13,English,,0,0,0,,ending the millennia-long tradition
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.44,0:17:32.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,结束了千年之久的将解决数学问题抽象成
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.13,0:17:35.45,English,,0,0,0,,of math problems as drawings and wordy descriptions.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.13,0:17:35.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,既要画画又要很啰嗦描述问题的习惯（？）
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.45,0:17:39.11,English,,0,0,0,,Geometry is no longer THE source of truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.45,0:17:39.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,几何学不再是真相的来源
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.20,0:17:44.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(287,533)\fad(500,500)}勒内·笛卡尔
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.00,0:17:42.41,English,,0,0,0,,makes heavy use of the square roots of negatives,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.00,0:17:42.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,经常使用负数平方根
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.41,0:17:44.70,English,,0,0,0,,popularizing them as a result.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.41,0:17:44.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使它们被广泛认知
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:46.69,English,,0,0,0,,And while he recognizes their utility,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.70,0:17:46.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在他识别它们的效用的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:50.33,English,,0,0,0,,he calls them imaginary numbers, a name that sticks,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.69,0:17:50.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他将它们称为虚数，一个固定的名字（？）
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:52.74,English,,0,0,0,,which is why Euler later introduces the letter i
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.74,0:17:55.33,English,,0,0,0,,to represent the square root of negative one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.33,0:17:55.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这也是为什么在之后欧拉将字幕i引入来表示这个负平方根
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.33,0:17:57.23,English,,0,0,0,,When combined with regular numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.33,0:17:57.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当虚数与实数结合在一起的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.23,0:17:59.90,English,,0,0,0,,they form complex numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.23,0:17:59.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它们形成了复数
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.90,0:18:02.67,English,,0,0,0,,The cubic led to the invention of these new numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.90,0:18:02.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,三次方程促进了这些新数的发明
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.67,0:18:05.83,English,,0,0,0,,and liberated algebra from geometry.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.67,0:18:05.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并把代数从几何中解放出来
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:09.41,English,,0,0,0,,By letting go of what seems like the best description of reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:09.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,扬弃了这些可见可感、
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.41,0:18:12.06,English,,0,0,0,,the geometry you can see and touch,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.41,0:18:12.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,表面上最符合现实的几何描述后
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:14.81,English,,0,0,0,,you get a much more powerful and complete mathematics
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.06,0:18:14.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,得到了一个适于求解真实问题的数学体系
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.81,0:18:17.13,English,,0,0,0,,that can solve real problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.81,0:18:17.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它更加强大和完整
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.13,0:18:20.77,English,,0,0,0,,And it turns out the cubic is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.13,0:18:20.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上三次方程仅仅是一个开始
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.77,0:18:21.90,English,,0,0,0,,In 1925,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.77,0:18:21.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在1925年
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.65,0:18:27.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(343,533)\fad(333,500)}埃尔文·薛定谔
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.82,0:18:24.95,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}is searching for a wave equation
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.82,0:18:24.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}正在寻找一个波动方程
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:27.41,English,,0,0,0,,{\an3}that governs the behavior of quantum particles
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.95,0:18:27.41,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an3}以此描述粒子行为的量子性
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.41,0:18:31.19,English,,0,0,0,,building on de Broglie's insight that matter consists of waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.41,0:18:31.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,基于德布罗意  有关波的本质的深刻见解
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.19,0:18:33.50,English,,0,0,0,,He comes up with one of the most important
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.50,0:18:35.96,English,,0,0,0,,and famous equations in all of physics,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.19,0:18:35.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他提出了物理学史上最重要而著名的方程之一
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.96,0:18:37.77,English,,0,0,0,,the Schrödinger equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.96,0:18:37.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,薛定谔方程
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:40.77,English,,0,0,0,,And featured prominently within it is i,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.77,0:18:40.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个方程最主要的特点是它含有 i
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:43.22,English,,0,0,0,,the square root of negative one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.77,0:18:43.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,负一的平方根
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:46.38,English,,0,0,0,,While mathematicians have grown accustomed to imaginary numbers,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.22,0:18:46.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当数学家已经习惯于虚数的存在时
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.38,0:18:47.74,English,,0,0,0,,physicists have not
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.38,0:18:47.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,物理学家还没有
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.74,0:18:49.56,English,,0,0,0,,and are uncomfortable seeing it show up
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.74,0:18:49.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虚数在这些基本理论中的出现
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:51.50,English,,0,0,0,,in such a fundamental theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:51.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,给他们带来了不适
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.50,0:18:53.27,English,,0,0,0,,Schrödinger himself writes
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.50,0:18:53.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,薛定谔自己写道
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.27,0:18:54.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这里 让人不快
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.69,0:18:57.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,并且显然会被反对的是
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.37,0:18:59.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,使用了虚数
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.64,0:19:04.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,波函数 ψ 根本而言无疑是一个实函数
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.76,0:19:06.74,English,,0,0,0,,This seems like a fair objection,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.76,0:19:06.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这看起来是一条恰当的反对意见
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:08.73,English,,0,0,0,,so why does an imaginary number
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.73,0:19:11.01,English,,0,0,0,,that first appeared in the solution to the cubic
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.74,0:19:11.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以首先在三次方程解当中出现的虚数
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.01,0:19:13.56,English,,0,0,0,,turn up in fundamental physics?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.01,0:19:13.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,为什么会进入基础物理的方程中呢
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.56,0:19:16.49,English,,0,0,0,,Well, it's because of some unique properties
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.49,0:19:18.51,English,,0,0,0,,of imaginary numbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.56,0:19:18.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是因为虚数某些独一无二的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.51,0:19:22.12,English,,0,0,0,,Imaginary numbers exist on a dimension perpendicular
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.12,0:19:23.92,English,,0,0,0,,to the real number line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.51,0:19:23.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虚数位于与实轴正交的方向上
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.92,0:19:27.16,English,,0,0,0,,Together, they form the complex plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.92,0:19:27.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,两者共同构成了复平面
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.16,0:19:30.80,English,,0,0,0,,Watch what happens when we repeatedly multiply by i.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.16,0:19:30.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看看我们重复乘以 i 会发生什么
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.80,0:19:32.33,English,,0,0,0,,Starting with one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.80,0:19:32.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从 1 开始
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.33,0:19:34.81,English,,0,0,0,,One times i is i,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.33,0:19:34.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,1 × i = 1
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:38.10,English,,0,0,0,,i times i is negative one, by definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.81,0:19:38.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,根据定义 i × i = -1
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.10,0:19:41.01,English,,0,0,0,,Negative one times i is negative i,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.10,0:19:41.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-1 × i = -i
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.01,0:19:43.63,English,,0,0,0,,and negative i times i is one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.01,0:19:43.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,-i × i = 1
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.63,0:19:45.05,English,,0,0,0,,We've come back to where we started,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.63,0:19:45.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们已经回到了开始的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.05,0:19:46.74,English,,0,0,0,,and if we keep multiplying by i,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.05,0:19:46.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果我们继续乘以 i
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.74,0:19:49.25,English,,0,0,0,,the point will keep rotating around.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.74,0:19:49.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,复平面上的点就会绕原点转圈
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:51.30,English,,0,0,0,,So when you're multiplying by i,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.25,0:19:51.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以做这样的乘法
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.30,0:19:53.83,English,,0,0,0,,what you're really doing is rotating
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.83,0:19:56.80,English,,0,0,0,,by 90 degrees in the complex plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.30,0:19:56.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上相当于在复平面上转过 90°
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.80,0:20:00.30,English,,0,0,0,,Now, there is a function that repeatedly multiplies by i
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.80,0:20:00.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在假设有一个函数 沿着 x 轴方向
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.30,0:20:02.42,English,,0,0,0,,as you go down the X-axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.30,0:20:02.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的值反复地乘以 i
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.42,0:20:05.46,English,,0,0,0,,And that is e to the ix.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.42,0:20:05.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这就是 e^ix
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.46,0:20:08.56,English,,0,0,0,,It creates a spiral by essentially spreading out
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.46,0:20:08.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它沿着 x 轴伸展
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.56,0:20:12.07,English,,0,0,0,,these rotations all along the X-axis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.56,0:20:12.07,Chinese,,0,0,0,,产生了一条绕 x 轴旋转的螺旋线
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.07,0:20:14.03,English,,0,0,0,,If you look at the real part of the spiral,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.07,0:20:14.03,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果观察这条螺旋线的实部
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.03,0:20:15.63,English,,0,0,0,,it's a cosine wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.03,0:20:15.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是余弦波
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.63,0:20:19.12,English,,0,0,0,,And if you look at the imaginary part, it's a sine wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.63,0:20:19.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你观察虚部 这是正弦波
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.12,0:20:22.16,English,,0,0,0,,The two quintessential functions that describe waves
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.12,0:20:22.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,用于描述波动的最典型的两个函数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.16,0:20:25.13,English,,0,0,0,,are both contained in e to the ix.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.16,0:20:25.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,都被包括在 e^ix 之中
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.21,0:20:28.77,English,,0,0,0,,So when Schrodinger goes to write down a wave equation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.21,0:20:28.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以当薛定谔写下波动方程的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.77,0:20:31.75,English,,0,0,0,,he naturally assumes that the solutions to his equation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.77,0:20:31.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他自然假设了他的方程的解
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:33.86,English,,0,0,0,,will look something like e to the ix,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.75,0:20:33.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,会取类似 e^ix 的形式
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.86,0:20:37.42,English,,0,0,0,,specifically e to the ikx minus omega t.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.86,0:20:37.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,准确地说 是 e^i(kx-ωt)
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.42,0:20:40.45,English,,0,0,0,,You might wonder why he would use that formulation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.42,0:20:40.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你也许会问他为什么会用这个公式
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.45,0:20:42.67,English,,0,0,0,,and not just a simple sine wave,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.45,0:20:42.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而非一个简单的正弦波
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.67,0:20:45.44,English,,0,0,0,,but the exponential has some useful properties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.67,0:20:45.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,指数函数有些有用的性质
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.44,0:20:48.89,English,,0,0,0,,If you take the derivative with respect to position or time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.44,0:20:48.89,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你对上式求关于位置或时间的导数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.89,0:20:50.56,English,,0,0,0,,that derivative is proportional
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.89,0:20:50.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,导函数将
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:52.79,English,,0,0,0,,to the original function itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.56,0:20:52.79,Chinese,,0,0,0,,正比于原函数本身
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.79,0:20:55.61,English,,0,0,0,,And that's not true if you use the sine function
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.79,0:20:55.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这点对正弦函数并不成立
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.61,0:20:57.76,English,,0,0,0,,whose derivative is cosine.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.61,0:20:57.76,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的导数是余弦函数
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.76,0:21:00.64,English,,0,0,0,,Plus, since the Schrodinger equation is linear,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.76,0:21:00.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,此外 由于薛定谔方程是线性的
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.64,0:21:03.39,English,,0,0,0,,you can add together an arbitrary number of solutions
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.64,0:21:03.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以将任意多这样的解叠加起来
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.39,0:21:07.31,English,,0,0,0,,of this form, creating any sort of wave shape you like,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.39,0:21:07.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,得到任何你想要的波形
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.31,0:21:10.67,English,,0,0,0,,and it too, will be a solution to Schrodinger's equation.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.31,0:21:10.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,其结果也是薛定谔方程解
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.67,0:21:13.43,English,,0,0,0,,The physicist Freeman Dyson later writes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.67,0:21:13.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,物理学家弗里曼·戴森随后写道
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.43,0:21:16.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,薛定谔将负一的平方根置入方程
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.64,0:21:18.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这一切突然有了意义
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.81,0:21:21.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它马上从一个热传导方程
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.19,0:21:23.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变成了一个波动方程
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.34,0:21:25.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an7}而薛定谔不无喜悦地发现
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.64,0:21:29.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an7}这个方程具有与玻尔原子模型中
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.31,0:21:31.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\an7}量子化轨道相对应的解
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.56,0:21:34.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这说明薛定谔方程正确地描述了
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.92,0:21:38.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们对原子的行为所知道的一切
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.29,0:21:42.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这是一切化学和许多物理学的根基
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.60,0:21:44.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,方程中负一的平方根
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.20,0:21:50.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,意味着自然凭借复数而非实数来运转
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.34,0:21:56.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对于薛定谔和其他所有人\N这项发现是个彻头彻尾的惊喜
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.98,0:21:58.63,English,,0,0,0,,So imaginary numbers
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.98,0:21:58.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以虚数
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.63,0:22:01.44,English,,0,0,0,,discovered as a quirky, intermediate step
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.63,0:22:01.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,本是作为一个古怪的中间步骤
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.44,0:22:03.20,English,,0,0,0,,on the way to solving the cubic
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.44,0:22:03.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,出现在三次方程的解当中
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.20,0:22:07.23,English,,0,0,0,,turn out to be fundamental to our description of reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.20,0:22:07.23,Chinese,,0,0,0,,却被发现是我们描述现实的基石
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.23,0:22:10.53,English,,0,0,0,,Only by giving up maths connection to reality
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.23,0:22:10.53,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只有放下数学与现实的关联
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.53,0:22:11.43,English,,0,0,0,,could it guide us
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.53,0:22:11.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我们才能走向
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.43,0:22:15.45,English,,0,0,0,,to a deeper truth about the way the universe works.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.43,0:22:15.45,Chinese,,0,0,0,,事关万物运行的深刻真理
